Final: Question 6

Which of these statements is true?

Note: to get a multiple answer question right in this final you must get all the components right, so even if
some parts are simple, take your time.


    -- MongoDB (v2.2) supports transactions spanning multiple documents, if those documents all reside 
    on the same shard.

    ANS: +check+ MongoDB supports atomic operations on individual documents.

    -- MongoDB allows you to change the storage engine on a collection level.

    ANS: +check+ MongoDB has a data type for dates and datetime data.
